305803571.text: "Activation of mechanistic target of rapamycin (mTOR) leads to suppression of autophagy via phosphorylation of multiple autophagy related proteins such as ULK1 (UNC-5 like autophagy activating kinase 1), ATG13 (autophagy related gene 13), AMBRA1 (autophagy and beclin 1 regulator 1), and ATG14L (baclin 1 associated autophagy related key regulator) [XREF_BIBR]."
